  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 / reuse mandate">MUST use the EXISTING `@spaarke/auth` `useAuth()` hook + `authenticatedFetch` function for ALL outbound HTTP. MUST NOT introduce a parallel auth client, a parallel token-acquisition path, a parallel BFF base-URL resolver, a parallel Bearer-header injector, or a new `fetch` wrapper. The auth library already handles: Bearer-header attachment, BFF base-URL resolution, 401 retry with exponential backoff, RFC 7807 ProblemDetails parsing, and broadcast-channel logout coordination. Reuse all of it.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028 / R5 CLAUDE.md §10 no-token-snapshot">MUST NOT snapshot tokens. `useAuth()` returns a `getAccessToken: () =&gt; Promise&lt;string&gt;` and an `authenticatedFetch` function — both re-acquire fresh tokens from the provider's cache on every call (per `useAuth.ts` comment lines 35–46). The Insights client wrapper MUST call `authenticatedFetch` directly per request (or call `getAccessToken()` per request for SSE — the narrow escape hatch documented in `useAuth.ts` for `ReadableStream` lifecycle). MUST NOT cache the token in a closure, module-level variable, React state, or any other persistent surface. Verified by Test 4 (simulated token rotation mid-call sequence).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.5 / ADR-013 §3.5 Zone B boundary">R5 is a Zone B consumer of the Insights HTTP contract. This task is purely Zone B (frontend consumption). MUST NOT import any types from `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/` or `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Insights/` — these are server-internal. Define local TypeScript types (request/response DTOs) that mirror the contract v1.0 shape per integration brief §3 + §4. Use `[key: string]: unknown` index signatures or `Record&lt;string, unknown&gt;` passthrough on response DTOs for v1.1 forward-compat (`citations[].href`, additional SSE fields).</constraint>
    <constraint source="contract v1.0 §3 (subject format)">Subject string format is `&lt;scheme&gt;:&lt;guid&gt;` where scheme is exactly `matter` / `project` / `invoice` (lowercase). GUID is the entity record ID with braces stripped (`launch-resolver.ts` already strips braces on inbound — preserve that discipline). Logical-name mapping is one-way: `sprk_matter` → `matter`, `sprk_project` → `project`, `sprk_invoice` → `invoice`. Any other logical name (or no entity in context) → `no-subject` sentinel. MUST NOT silently coerce or default to `matter` — that hides bugs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="contract v1.0 §3.1 (query length)">Tool accepts `query` parameter (required, 1..500 chars). Client does NOT pre-truncate or pre-validate — the BFF returns 400 `query.required` for empty/whitespace and rejects oversize via ProblemDetails. Pass through unchanged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-17 / SC-16 (correlation-id propagation)">MUST generate a unique `x-correlation-id` per outbound call using `crypto.randomUUID()`. MUST set it as an HTTP request header on the call. MUST return it on the success result + on the typed error so the caller (chat-pane orchestration / renderer task 026) can surface it in UX + log it for App Insights / Kusto end-to-end correlation. Verified by Test 5.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-16 (12 error codes) / ADR-019 (ProblemDetails parsing)">MUST parse non-2xx responses as `application/problem+json` per RFC 7807 + ADR-019 — `authenticatedFetch` already throws `ApiError` carrying `problemDetails`; extract the contract's 5 fields (`errorCode`, `correlationId`, `status`, `title`, `detail`) and re-throw a typed `InsightsQueryError`. Preserve all 12 contract error codes (integration brief §5.1): `query.required`, `subject.required`, `subject.invalid`, `forceMode.invalid`, `conversationContext.invalid`, `ai.insights.disabled`, `ai.rag.disabled`, `ai.intent-classification.disabled`, `ai.assistant-default-playbook.unconfigured`, `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR`, plus `auth.401` (synthetic) + `rate-limit.429` (synthetic with Retry-After).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-11 / contract v1.1 forward-compat (SSE + 406 fallback)">MUST send `Accept: text/event-stream` to opt into v1.1 SSE. If server returns 406 (v1.0-only deployment), fall back to a second request with `Accept: application/json` and parse the v1.0 single-shot envelope. The fallback is BINDING regardless of Wave F deploy timing — Wave F may slip, may revert, or may co-deploy with R5 Phase 2 at any timing. The graceful-fallback behavior MUST work on day 1 of Phase 2.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-12 / SC-17 (forceMode semantics)">Client accepts optional `forceMode: 'playbook' | 'rag'` parameter. Forwards unchanged to the BFF (or omits when undefined). MUST NOT default `forceMode` itself — the slash command path (task 019) sets it explicitly; the LLM tool-call path leaves it absent. Invalid values surface as the contract's 400 `forceMode.invalid` from the BFF.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016 (rate-limit honoring)">On 429, surface the structured error (with `Retry-After` value extracted from response headers if present) — do NOT auto-retry in this client. The chat-agent orchestration (task 029) owns retry policy across the broader Insights surface.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-12 / ADR-019 (no content leakage in errors)">Errors NEVER include document content, prompt text, LLM raw output, or stack traces in the structured error returned to the caller. The 5 ProblemDetails fields are the ONLY information surfaced. `console.error` logging is allowed and includes correlationId for ops debugging.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 / R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (no BFF code changed by this task). Confirm in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 / project test obligation">PRs creating new frontend modules MUST add unit tests. Test paths follow `__tests__/` colocated convention used elsewhere in the SpaarkeAi project (e.g., `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/context/__tests__/ContextPaneController.test.tsx`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-031 / R5 §3 (shell stage context)">Subject resolution reads from the SpaarkeAi launch params (URL + `App.tsx` `entityLogicalName` / `entityId` / `matterId` props per `launch-resolver.ts`). MAY also consult `useShellStage()` for stage-aware behavior (e.g., emit `no-subject` during `welcome` stage). Do NOT re-derive entity context from a parallel source — the launch-resolver contract is the canonical inbound entry per spec §8.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.4 (PaneEventBus discipline)">This task does NOT add new PaneEventBus channels and does NOT add new event types beyond those already declared in §3.4 (additive event types only). Subject resolution is a synchronous read of mount-time launch params — no event-driven coupling needed.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>frontend/auth-library-consumption + frontend/zone-b-http-consumption</topic>
    <files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Auth/src/index.ts</file>
