    <step order="8" name="Update slash command path consumer signature (informational only — no code change)">
      This task does NOT modify task 019's slash command code. Record the
      integration contract in `notes/task-025-evidence.md` so task 019
      (parallel-safe sibling P2-G5; may already be implemented or in
      flight) has a clean consumption recipe. The contract:

      ```ts
      // Inside /ask-insights slash command handler (task 019 surface):
      import { resolveSubject, callInsightsQuery, InsightsQueryError }
        from '../services/insightsQueryClient';

      const subjectResult = resolveSubject(entityLogicalName, entityId);
      if (subjectResult.kind === 'no-subject') {
        // Surface client-side `subject.required` to chat pane
        emit({ kind: 'error', errorCode: 'subject.required',
               detail: 'No entity in chat context.' });
        return;
      }
      try {
        const result = await callInsightsQuery({
          query: userQuery,
          subject: subjectResult.subject,
          forceMode: slashSubCommand === 'playbook' ? 'playbook'
                   : slashSubCommand === 'rag' ? 'rag' : undefined,
        });
        // Hand off to renderer (task 026):
        renderInsightsResponse(result);
      } catch (err) {
        if (err instanceof InsightsQueryError) {
          // Per-code UX (task 026's renderer): integration brief §5.1 column 4
          renderInsightsError(err);
        } else { throw err; }
      }
      ```
