  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Module `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/services/insightsQueryClient.ts` exists and exports `resolveSubject`, `callInsightsQuery`, `InsightsQueryError`, plus the 5 supporting types (`SubjectScheme`, `ResolvedSubject`, `NoSubject`, `InsightsQueryRequest`, `InsightsQueryResult`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`resolveSubject` correctly maps `sprk_matter` → `matter`, `sprk_project` → `project`, `sprk_invoice` → `invoice`; any other logical name OR missing entityId returns `{ kind: 'no-subject' }`; braces are stripped defensively; canonical subject format is `&lt;scheme&gt;:&lt;guid&gt;`. Confirmed by Tests 1 + 2.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`callInsightsQuery` POSTs to `/api/insights/assistant/query` via the EXISTING `@spaarke/auth` `authenticatedFetch` — no parallel auth client; reuse mandate satisfied (R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Authorization header is set with a fresh token per call via `authenticatedFetch` (NOT snapshotted in module-level state, closure, or React state). Confirmed by Test 4 (simulated token rotation between two sequential calls).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`x-correlation-id` request header is generated via `crypto.randomUUID()` per call, propagated outbound, and returned to the caller on both success (`result.correlationId`) and error (`InsightsQueryError.correlationId`). Two sequential calls produce two distinct IDs. Confirmed by Test 5. (spec FR-17 / SC-16)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">v1.1 SSE consumption works: when server returns 200 + `Content-Type: text/event-stream`, the client parses incremental SSE events (`metadata`, `delta`, `complete`) and resolves to the assembled envelope. Confirmed by Test 3.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">v1.0 JSON path works directly when server returns 200 + `Content-Type: application/json` (no fallback needed). Confirmed by Test 6.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">406 fallback to v1.0 JSON works: when first call (with `Accept: text/event-stream`) returns 406, client retries once with `Accept: application/json` reusing the same `x-correlation-id`. Confirmed by Test 7. (spec NFR-11 graceful fallback)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 12 contract error codes from integration brief §5.1 surface as `InsightsQueryError` preserving `errorCode`, `correlationId`, `status`, `title`, `detail`, plus `retryAfterSeconds` for `rate-limit.429`. Codes verified: `query.required`, `subject.required`, `subject.invalid`, `forceMode.invalid`, `conversationContext.invalid`, `auth.401` (synthetic), `rate-limit.429` (synthetic), `ai.insights.disabled`, `ai.rag.disabled`, `ai.intent-classification.disabled`, `ai.assistant-default-playbook.unconfigured`, `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR`. Confirmed by Test 8. (spec FR-16)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`forceMode` parameter works: `undefined` → field omitted from request body; `'playbook'` and `'rag'` → field forwarded; client does NOT pre-validate or default. Confirmed by Test 9. (spec FR-12 / SC-17)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">v1.1 forward-compat: unknown response fields (e.g., `citations[].href`, top-level SSE/streaming fields, `confidence`) pass through unchanged in `result.envelope` (`Record&lt;string, unknown&gt;` index-signature passthrough). Confirmed by Test 10.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Zone B boundary verified by explicit grep**: the new module file contains ZERO `import ... from 'src/server/api/...'` and ZERO references to server-internal Insights namespaces. Confirmed by Test 11 + reviewer inspection at Step 9.5. (R5 CLAUDE.md §3.5 + §10)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">AbortSignal cancellation supported: passing a `signal` from an `AbortController` to `callInsightsQuery` aborts the in-flight call. Confirmed by Test 12.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">429 surfaced structurally with `Retry-After` extracted; no in-client auto-retry; chat orchestration (task 029) owns retry policy. Confirmed by Test 8 `rate-limit.429` case. (ADR-016)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ZERO new auth primitives / wrappers / strategies introduced (R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1); ZERO new feature flags (R5 §3.2); ZERO new PaneEventBus channels (R5 §3.4); ZERO BFF code modified. Confirmed by reviewer inspection + `git diff` showing only frontend file additions.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (frontend-only task; no BFF code modified). Recorded in `notes/task-025-evidence.md`. (R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 12 unit tests pass via `npm test`; `tsc --noEmit` is clean. Recorded in `notes/task-025-evidence.md`.</criterion>
